 mills in the United Kingdom|Huddersfield]]\n[[Category:Former textile mills in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:History of the textile industry]]\n[[Category:Industrial Revolution in England]]\n", "name_user": "Schlosser67", "label": "safe", "comment": "(GR)File renamed:File:Brittania Mills 1835.JPG\u2192File:Britannia Mills 1835.jpgCriterion 3typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_mills_in_Huddersfield"}
{"title_page": "Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain", "text_new": "\n\n[[File:Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain, The Tank, March 2019.jpg|thumb|right|N\u00ed R\u00edain at [[The Tank (theater)|The Tank]] in 2019 for the US premiere of ''The Tallest Man in the World''|alt=A woman with short blonde hair and black glasses wears a gray coat and shoulder-strap bag and stands facing the camera before a gray wall.]]\n'''Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain''' (born 15 June 1974) is an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[composer]] and [[playwright]].<ref>Johanne Heraty, \"N\u00ed R\u00edain, Ail\u00eds\", in: ''The Encyclopaedia of Music in Ireland'', ed. Harry White and Barra Boydell (Dublin: UCD Press, 2013), pp. 735\u2013736.</ref>\n\n==Music==\nBorn in [[Cork (city)|Cork]], N\u00ed R\u00edain was formally trained in [[classical music]] as a composer and [[pianist]]. She was awarded the [[Paul Hamlyn]] Award for Composers in November 2016. She studied at The Royal Northern College of Music, Manchester University, the University of York and University College Cork. Her music has been broadcast on [[BBC Radio 3]], [[RTE]] and [[BBC Radio 4]] and performed in Europe, Israel, Brazil and the United States.\n\nAs a pianist she has an interest in extended piano techniques, prepared piano and piano alterations. She has been a Fellow at the Ragdale Foundation, Illinois, USA, Virginia Center for the Arts, the Irish Cultural Centre in Paris and the Atlantic Center for the Arts in Florida.\n\nHer debut album, a Bront\u00eb concept album ''Linger'', was released in 2015 alongside a music installation for the Bront\u00eb Parsonage in Yorkshire.\n\nShe is represented by the Contemporary Music Centre, Dublin. The British Music Collection also holds a selection of her musical work.\n\n==Writing==\nN\u00ed R\u00edain's literary work is published by Bloomsbury and Nick Hern Books. Her first play, ''BEATEN'', premiered in Liverpool in 2007, was published as ''Tilt'' by Nick Hern Books. ''Desolate Heaven'' was produced by Theatre503 in 2013 and published by Methuen Drama. ''The Tallest Man in the World'' was premiered by Corcadorca Theatre Company in Cork, Ireland, in 2014 and shortlisted for the Eugene O'Neill Playwright's Conference, USA. The American premiere of ''The Tallest Man in the World'' took place at The Tank Theater in New York in March 2019.\n\n==List of Works==\n===Solo===\n* ''Our First Lesson in Forgetting'' (2019), for guitar\n* ''Anomaly'' (2019), for toy piano\n* ''Loophole'' (2018), for saxophone\n* ''The Height of Me'' (2018), for piano\n* ''Terpsichore'' (2018), for cello\n* ''Soberado'' (2017), for toy piano\n* ''A Black Hole of Idiocy'' (2016), for accordion\n* ''Skloni\u0161te'' (2016), 9 pieces for accordion [& video]\n* ''Linger'' (2015), 6 pieces for piano\n* ''Not About Heroes'' (2014), 6 pieces for cello\n* ''When I die, you can do what you want'' (2014), for violin [with video by Adela Jusic]\n* ''Treasured'' (2012), 7 pieces for trumpet\n* ''Beautiful Cracked Eyes'' (2008), for piano\n* ''Surrealist Pilgrims'' (2007), for amplified cello & tape\n* ''Into the Sea of Waking Dreams ...'' (2007), 4 pieces for piano with optional texts\n* ''2 Steep 4 Sheep (some hills are)'' (2006), for amplified harpsichord and fixed audio\n* ''The Falling'' (2005), 2 pieces for harp\n* ''Fwd: [no subject]'' (2003), for trumpet\n* ''Rude Boy'' (2002), for piano\n* ''Flat-Footed-Former-Flyer'' (2002), for trombone\n* ''Dogs in Waiting'' (1999), 7 pieces for double-bass\n\n===Duo===\n''Highfalutin'' (2017) 2 mins\nTwo flutes\n\n''Consent #7''  (2017) 7 mins\nBass-flute and Bass-clarinet\n\n''The Consequences of Falling'' (2013) 12 mins\nDouble-bass & trumpet\n\n''Chainstitchembroidered'' (2012) 14 mins\nFlute & piano\n\n''Quantitas Speaks'' (2012) 12 mins\nPiano duo & tape\n\n''End with Words of Hope'' (2010) 9 mins\n9 pieces for soprano, clarinet (& optional speaker)\n\n''Brief-Blue-Electric-Bloom'' (2010) 35 mins\n6 pieces two guitars (acoustic or electric)\n\n''10,000 Deviants'' (2007) 5 mins\nFlute, piano (& optional speaker)\n\n''FIRST ABSOLUTE EXECUTION'' (2004) 11 mins\n5 pieces for bass-clarinet & accordion\n\n''DON\u2019T!'' (2000) 4 mins\nBass-clarinet & cello\n\n''The Man Made of Rain'' (1999) 10 mins\nClarinet/speaker & piano\n\n''Mercury'' (1997) 5 mins\nViolin & piano\n\n''Down the Rabbit Hole'' (1994) 8 mins\nFlute & piano\n\n=== Trio ===\n\n''Soundless'' (2016) 6 mins\nViolin, oboe, tenor recorder\n\n''Reinventions'' (2010) 18 mins\n7 pieces for clarinet, viola, piano (optional texts/speaker)\n\n''UPTHEWALLS'' (2007) 5 mins\nTrumpet, drumkit, double-bass\n\n''Rogue Boar Shot Dead'' (2007) 7 mins\nTrumpet, drum-Kit, piano\n\n''The Last Time I Died\u2026'' (2002) 6 mins\nViolin, piano, percussion\n\n''Under the Rose\u2026'' (2000) 10 mins\n4 pieces for flute, violin, piano\n\n=== Quartets & Quintets ===\n\n''Dubinina\u2019s Tongue'' (2015) 10 mins\nPercussion Quartet for 4 bowed cymbals & video\n\n''Treasured Suite'' (2012) 12 mins\n5 pieces for brass quintet\n\n''Orizzontale'' (1997) 9 mins\nViolin, clarinet, cello, piano, perc\n\n=== Chamber Ensemble ===\n\n''Seal\u00e1n'' (2017) 5 mins\nOpen Score commission for COMA.\nHigh, mid-high, mid-low, low with percussion and piano.\n\n''The Dead Live'' (2002) 14 mins\nPiccolo, bass-clarinet, oboe, bassoon, horn, cello, piano,\nharp, double-bass, perc & 6 pairs of glasses\n\n''METRO'' (2001) 3 mins\nWind band with electric bass guitar\n\n=== Music-Theatre ===\n\n''I Used to Feel\u2026'' (2016) 16 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nClarinet & sign-language performer.\n\n''Treasured'' (2012) 90 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nSolo trumpet, brass quintet, 6 actors.\n\n''Brief-Blue-Electric-Bloom'' (2010) 60 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nGuitar x2, sign-language performers, animation & fixed media voice.\n\n''The Falling'' (2005) 55 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nHarp, electroacoustic score with text.\n\n''EXIT'' (2003) 50 mins\nMixed vocal sextet, flute, clarinet, violin, guitar, harp\nvibes, double-bass/electric, perc.\n\n=== Vocal ===\n\n''A Crow\u2019s Wisp/Sop Pr\u00e9ach\u00e1in'' (2019) 12 mins\nText by Aifric Mac Aodha\nSoprano and piano\n\n''Break Down De Doom'' (2017) 27 mins\nMusic by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nText by Mac Wellman\nMezzo-sop, flute, violin, viola, cello\n\n''Song of Letters'' (2016) 6 mins\nSoprano &Trumpet\nText by Caroline Clegg\n\n''Cimmerian'' (2015) 5 mins\nSoprano\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Eyeless'' (2012) 14 mins\nFolk singer and choir\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain (in Irish & English)\n\n''In Sleep\u2026'' (2010) 15 mins\nMezzo-soprano, flt, clar, bassoon, tpt, trom, pf, perc\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Valley of Stone'' (2008) 5 mins\nMale voice choir\n\n''Spurious Balancing'' (2003) 5 mins\nCounter-tenor, tenor, baritone\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Attrition'' (2001) 14 mins\nSoprano & piano\nSong cycle in 4 movements\nText by Kenneth Clarke\n\n''A Song for My Body'' (1998) 12 mins\nSoprano, flute, trumpet, cello, piano, perc.\nText by Christy Brown\n\n''Songs for Soprano'' (1995/6) 5 mins\nShe Tells Her Love\nThis Moment\nChild Of Our Time\n\n=== Fixed Audio ===\n\n''Pulse Prelude I'' (2011) 2 mins\n\n''TranSextreme'' (2007) 6 mins\n\n''StreetSong'' (2007) 5 mins\n\n''But Will You?'' (2006) 5 mins\n\n''Wounds, Scars, Screams'' (2005) 6 mins\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* http://www.irishwriters-online.com/ni-riain-ailis/\n* https://www.ailis.info/\n* http://journalofmusic.com/news/ailis-ni-riain-receives-ps50k-paul-hamlyn-award\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:N\u00ed R\u00edain, Ail\u00eds}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish people]]\n[[Category:Irish classical composers]]\n[[Category:Irish dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Irish women writers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from County Cork]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n[[File:Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain, The Tank, March 2019.jpg|thumb|right|N\u00ed R\u00edain at [[The Tank (theater)|The Tank]] in 2019 for the US premiere of ''The Tallest Man in the World''|alt=A woman with short blonde hair and black glasses wears a gray coat and shoulder-strap bag and stands facing the camera before a gray wall.]]\n'''Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain''' (born 15 June 1974) is an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[composer]] and [[playwright]].<ref>Johanne Heraty, \"N\u00ed R\u00edain, Ail\u00eds\", in: ''The Encyclopaedia of Music in Ireland'', ed. Harry White and Barra Boydell (Dublin: UCD Press, 2013), pp. 735\u2013736.\n\n==Music==\nBorn in [[Cork (city)|Cork]], N\u00ed R\u00edain was formally trained in [[classical music]] as a composer and [[pianist]]. She was awarded the [[Paul Hamlyn]] Award for Composers in November 2016. She studied at The Royal Northern College of Music, Manchester University, the University of York and University College Cork. Her music has been broadcast on [[BBC Radio 3]], [[RTE]] and [[BBC Radio 4]] and performed in Europe, Israel, Brazil and the United States.\n\nAs a pianist she has an interest in extended piano techniques, prepared piano and piano alterations. She has been a Fellow at the Ragdale Foundation, Illinois, USA, Virginia Center for the Arts, the Irish Cultural Centre in Paris and the Atlantic Center for the Arts in Florida.\n\nHer debut album, a Bront\u00eb concept album ''Linger'', was released in 2015 alongside a music installation for the Bront\u00eb Parsonage in Yorkshire.\n\nShe is represented by the Contemporary Music Centre, Dublin. The British Music Collection also holds a selection of her musical work.\n\n==Writing==\nN\u00ed R\u00edain's literary work is published by Bloomsbury and Nick Hern Books. Her first play, ''BEATEN'', premiered in Liverpool in 2007, was published as ''Tilt'' by Nick Hern Books. ''Desolate Heaven'' was produced by Theatre503 in 2013 and published by Methuen Drama. ''The Tallest Man in the World'' was premiered by Corcadorca Theatre Company in Cork, Ireland, in 2014 and shortlisted for the Eugene O'Neill Playwright's Conference, USA. The American premiere of ''The Tallest Man in the World'' took place at The Tank Theater in New York in March 2019.\n\n==List of Works==\n===Solo===\n* ''Our First Lesson in Forgetting'' (2019), for guitar\n* ''Anomaly'' (2019), for toy piano\n* ''Loophole'' (2018), for saxophone\n* ''The Height of Me'' (2018), for piano\n* ''Terpsichore'' (2018), for cello\n* ''Soberado'' (2017), for toy piano\n* ''A Black Hole of Idiocy'' (2016), for accordion\n* ''Skloni\u0161te'' (2016), 9 pieces for accordion [& video]\n* ''Linger'' (2015), 6 pieces for piano\n* ''Not About Heroes'' (2014), 6 pieces for cello\n* ''When I die, you can do what you want'' (2014), for violin [with video by Adela Jusic]\n* ''Treasured'' (2012), 7 pieces for trumpet\n* ''Beautiful Cracked Eyes'' (2008), for piano\n* ''Surrealist Pilgrims'' (2007), for amplified cello & tape\n* ''Into the Sea of Waking Dreams ...'' (2007), 4 pieces for piano with optional texts\n* ''2 Steep 4 Sheep (some hills are)'' (2006), for amplified harpsichord and fixed audio\n* ''The Falling'' (2005), 2 pieces for harp\n* ''Fwd: [no subject]'' (2003), for trumpet\n* ''Rude Boy'' (2002), for piano\n* ''Flat-Footed-Former-Flyer'' (2002), for trombone\n* ''Dogs in Waiting'' (1999), 7 pieces for double-bass\n\n===Duo===\n''Highfalutin'' (2017) 2 mins\nTwo flutes\n\n''Consent #7''  (2017) 7 mins\nBass-flute and Bass-clarinet\n\n''The Consequences of Falling'' (2013) 12 mins\nDouble-bass & trumpet\n\n''Chainstitchembroidered'' (2012) 14 mins\nFlute & piano\n\n''Quantitas Speaks'' (2012) 12 mins\nPiano duo & tape\n\n''End with Words of Hope'' (2010) 9 mins\n9 pieces for soprano, clarinet (& optional speaker)\n\n''Brief-Blue-Electric-Bloom'' (2010) 35 mins\n6 pieces two guitars (acoustic or electric)\n\n''10,000 Deviants'' (2007) 5 mins\nFlute, piano (& optional speaker)\n\n''FIRST ABSOLUTE EXECUTION'' (2004) 11 mins\n5 pieces for bass-clarinet & accordion\n\n''DON\u2019T!'' (2000) 4 mins\nBass-clarinet & cello\n\n''The Man Made of Rain'' (1999) 10 mins\nClarinet/speaker & piano\n\n''Mercury'' (1997) 5 mins\nViolin & piano\n\n''Down the Rabbit Hole'' (1994) 8 mins\nFlute & piano\n\n=== Trio ===\n\n''Soundless'' (2016) 6 mins\nViolin, oboe, tenor recorder\n\n''Reinventions'' (2010) 18 mins\n7 pieces for clarinet, viola, piano (optional texts/speaker)\n\n''UPTHEWALLS'' (2007) 5 mins\nTrumpet, drumkit, double-bass\n\n''Rogue Boar Shot Dead'' (2007) 7 mins\nTrumpet, drum-Kit, piano\n\n''The Last Time I Died\u2026'' (2002) 6 mins\nViolin, piano, percussion\n\n''Under the Rose\u2026'' (2000) 10 mins\n4 pieces for flute, violin, piano\n\n=== Quartets & Quintets ===\n\n''Dubinina\u2019s Tongue'' (2015) 10 mins\nPercussion Quartet for 4 bowed cymbals & video\n\n''Treasured Suite'' (2012) 12 mins\n5 pieces for brass quintet\n\n''Orizzontale'' (1997) 9 mins\nViolin, clarinet, cello, piano, perc\n\n=== Chamber Ensemble ===\n\n''Seal\u00e1n'' (2017) 5 mins\nOpen Score commission for COMA.\nHigh, mid-high, mid-low, low with percussion and piano.\n\n''The Dead Live'' (2002) 14 mins\nPiccolo, bass-clarinet, oboe, bassoon, horn, cello, piano,\nharp, double-bass, perc & 6 pairs of glasses\n\n''METRO'' (2001) 3 mins\nWind band with electric bass guitar\n\n=== Music-Theatre ===\n\n''I Used to Feel\u2026'' (2016) 16 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nClarinet & sign-language performer.\n\n''Treasured'' (2012) 90 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nSolo trumpet, brass quintet, 6 actors.\n\n''Brief-Blue-Electric-Bloom'' (2010) 60 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nGuitar x2, sign-language performers, animation & fixed media voice.\n\n''The Falling'' (2005) 55 mins\nWritten & composed by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nHarp, electroacoustic score with text.\n\n''EXIT'' (2003) 50 mins\nMixed vocal sextet, flute, clarinet, violin, guitar, harp\nvibes, double-bass/electric, perc.\n\n=== Vocal ===\n\n''A Crow\u2019s Wisp/Sop Pr\u00e9ach\u00e1in'' (2019) 12 mins\nText by Aifric Mac Aodha\nSoprano and piano\n\n''Break Down De Doom'' (2017) 27 mins\nMusic by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\nText by Mac Wellman\nMezzo-sop, flute, violin, viola, cello\n\n''Song of Letters'' (2016) 6 mins\nSoprano &Trumpet\nText by Caroline Clegg\n\n''Cimmerian'' (2015) 5 mins\nSoprano\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Eyeless'' (2012) 14 mins\nFolk singer and choir\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain (in Irish & English)\n\n''In Sleep\u2026'' (2010) 15 mins\nMezzo-soprano, flt, clar, bassoon, tpt, trom, pf, perc\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Valley of Stone'' (2008) 5 mins\nMale voice choir\n\n''Spurious Balancing'' (2003) 5 mins\nCounter-tenor, tenor, baritone\nText by Ail\u00eds N\u00ed R\u00edain\n\n''Attrition'' (2001) 14 mins\nSoprano & piano\nSong cycle in 4 movements\nText by Kenneth Clarke\n\n''A Song for My Body'' (1998) 12 mins\nSoprano, flute, trumpet, cello, piano, perc.\nText by Christy Brown\n\n''Songs for Soprano'' (1995/6) 5 mins\nShe Tells Her Love\nThis Moment\nChild Of Our Time\n\n=== Fixed Audio ===\n\n''Pulse Prelude I'' (2011) 2 mins\n\n''TranSextreme'' (2007) 6 mins\n\n''StreetSong'' (2007) 5 mins\n\n''But Will You?'' (2006) 5 mins\n\n''Wounds, Scars, Screams'' (2005) 6 mins\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* http://www.irishwriters-online.com/ni-riain-ailis/\n* https://www.ailis.info/\n* http://journalofmusic.com/news/ailis-ni-riain-receives-ps50k-paul-hamlyn-award\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:N\u00ed R\u00edain, Ail\u00eds}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish people]]\n[[Category:Irish classical composers]]\n[[Category:Irish dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Irish women writers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from County Cork]]\n", "name_user": "Aklein62", "label": "safe", "comment": "ref", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ail%C3%ADs_N%C3%AD_R%C3%ADain"}
