      = Geert Bakker\n| image          = Geert A. Bakker (NED).png\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = Geert Alle Bakker\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = Dutch\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1921|01|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Appingedam]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|1993|08|07|1921|01|15|df=y}}\n| death_place    = [[Warmond]]\n| height         = {{convert|1.94|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| retired        = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = Koninklijke Watersport Vereniging <br /> De Kaag\n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport | [[Sailing (sport)|Sailing]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Championship]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | 1968 [[Copenhagen]] | [[Soling]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | 1979 [[La Rochelle]] | [[Soling]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[South American Championship]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | 1977 [[template:Soling South American Championship medallists|Rio de Janeiro]] | [[Soling]] }}\n| show-medals    = yes\n| updated        = 2019-11-7\n}}\n\n'''Geert Alle Bakker''' (15 January 1921 in [[Appingedam]] \u2013 7 August 1993 in [[Warmond]]) was a [[sailor]] from the [[Netherlands]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1976 Summer Olympics]] in [[Kingston, Ontario]], Canada. With crew [[Pieter Keijzer]] and [[Harald de Vlaming]] Bakker took the 5th place in the [[Soling]]. Since in [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1980]] The  Netherlands did [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycott]] the [[Moscow]] Olympic Games Bakker again in the Soling  represented his National Olympic Committee under the Dutch [[NOC*NSF|NOC]] flag. This time with crew [[Dick Coster]] and his son [[Steven Bakker]] They took again 5th place.\n\nFrom 1976 till 1979 Geert was president of the [[Soling|International Soling Association]]. After a brain stroke in 1983 he stayed close involved with Soling Sailing however he specialized in judging.\n\n==Controversy==\nSeveral countries did [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycott]] the [[Sailing at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]], others like [[France]] did not go since they found the competition devaluated. As result only half of the expected fleet was present during the Olympic regattas. It was the effort of Bakker and [[Ben Staartjes]] that the [[Dutch Olympic Sailing Team]] went to Tallinn.\n{{Footer Dutch Champions in Soling}}\n{{1980DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n{{1988DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n{{S-start}}\n  {{s-sports}} \n  {{S-bef|before = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Jack van Dyke]]}}\n  {{S-ttl|title  = [[International Soling Association|President International Soling Association]] | years=1975 - 1979}}\n  {{S-aft|after  = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Ken Berkeley]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Netherlands-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n==Sources==\n* {{cite web\n |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ba/geert-bakker-1.html \n |title=Geert Bakker Bio, Stats, and Results \n |publisher=Sports-Reference.com \n |work=Olympic Sports \n |accessdate=9 January 2014 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224113900/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ba/geert-bakker-1.html \n |archivedate=24 December 2013 \n |df=dmy \n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010620261:mpeg21:a0244\n  | title      = Nederlandse delegatie\n  | publisher  = Leeuwarder courant : hoofdblad van Friesland\n  | date       = 12 July 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 29 January 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011200804:mpeg21:a0338\n  | title      = Olympische zeilselectie\n  | publisher  = De Telegraaf\n  | date       = 20 May 1976\n  | language   = Dutch\n  | accessdate = 29 January 2014\n}}\n* {{cite web\n  | url        = http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1976/1976v1.pdf\n  | tit